: "Penlod"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Place of the Well"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Quenta Silmarillion (Lost Road)"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Road of Arches"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Road of Pomps"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Rog"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Salgant"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Seven Gates of Gondolin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Square of the Palace"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Sting"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Ted Nasmith"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Book of Lost Tales"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Fall of Gondolin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Fall of Gondolin (chapter)"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Lay of the Fall of Gondolin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Lost Road and Other Writings"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "The Silmarillion"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Thorondor"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tolkien"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tower of the King"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tumladen"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Tuor"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Turgon"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Twelve houses of the Gondothlim"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Ulmo"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Ulmo's warning"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Voronwë"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Wanderings of Húrin"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Warden of the Great Gate"}, {"ns": 0, "exists": "", "*": "Way of Running Waters"}, {"ns": 0, "*": "Iron Guards"}], "templates": [{"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:References"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:LR"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Webcite"}, {"ns": 10, "exists": "", "*": "Template:Gondolin"}], "images": ["Ted_Nasmith_-_Beren_and_Lúthien_are_Flown_to_Safety.jpg"], "wikitext": {"*": "[[File:Ted Nasmith - Beren and Lúthien are Flown to Safety.jpg|180px|thumb|''Beren and Lúthien are Flown to Safety'' by [[Ted Nasmith]]]]\n\nThe '''Eithel Nínui''', also called the '''Fountain of Tinúviel''', was a fountain found on the plain of [[Tumladen]]. It is said to have been created by the tears of [[Lúthien]] falling down on the plain when she and [[Beren]] were flown over it by [[Thorondor]] and his vassals. Its water was recounted in song as having had healing powers until it was destroyed in the [[Fall of Gondolin]].\n\n==Note on occurrence==\nThe fountain and its legend is found in one of [[Tolkien]]'s drafts of the ''[[Quenta Silmarillion (Lost Road)|Quenta Silmarillion]]'', but in the published version found in ''[[The Silmarillion]]'', [[Christopher Tolkien]] omitted it. He has later admitted that this section should have remained in the published work.<ref>{{LR|Quenta}}, p. 301</ref>\n\n==Etymology==\n''Eithel Nínui'' is [[Noldorin]], containing ''[[eithel]]'' (\"spring, well\") and ''[[nínui]]'' (\"tearful\", as proposed by [[Paul Strack]]).<ref>{{webcite|author=[[Paul Strack]]|articleurl=https://eldamo.org/content/words/word-679425019.html|articlename=N. ''Eithel Nínui'' loc.|website=Eldamo|accessed=11 October 2022}}</ref>\n\n{{references}}\n\n{{gondolin}}\n\n[[Category:Fountains]]\n[[Category:Gondolin]]\n[[Category:Noldorin locations]]\n[[Category:Springs and wells]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Eithel Niniu}}\n[[fi:Eithel Nínui]]"}}}